   "source": [
    "Python's Built-In Iterables and Iterators - Lecture"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "63e7c1e0-0360-415a-bb1e-26c968b9d607",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Python provides many functions that return iterables or iterators\n",
    "Additionally, the iterators perform lazy evaluation\n",
    "You shoul always be aware of whether you are dealing with iterable or iterator\n",
    "- if an object is an iterable (but not an iterator) you can iterate over it many times\n",
    "- if an object is an iterator you can iterate over it only once"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "e902de60-b2eb-44e0-9801-152070c8a326",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "range(10) -> iterable\n",
    "zip(l1, l2) -> iterator\n",
    "enumerate(l1) -> iterator\n",
    "open('cars.csv') -> iterator\n",
    "dictionary.keys() -> iterable\n",
    "dictionary.values() -> iterable\n",
    "dictionary.items() -> iterable\n",
    "\n",
    "many more..."
   ]
  },
  {
